        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>The new PvP server (according to the article at <a href="http://www.lumthemad.net/news/2004.php)" target="_blank">www.lumthemad.net/news/2004.php)</a> is not supposed to be pure deity-based, but deity-teams: Good, Neutral, Evil. Which is good for an aspiring Evil Iksar guild, since a Cazic-Thule only guild would have some big deficiencies. No rogues. No INT casters other than necros. Only Erudite clerics and Troll and Iksar shamen for "support" classes.</P><P>Since that would not seem to be the case based on what Lum quoted Abashi saying, I did a quick sort into good, neutral, and evil by religion: If the religion had paladins, it was good. Shadow knights, evil. Neither, neutral. Based on that...</P><P>Good: Karana, both Marrs, Rodcet Nife, Prexus, Quellious, Brell Serlis, Tunare. Classes unavailable: Necro, SK, shaman.</P><P>Neutral: Bristlebane, Solusek Ro, Tribunal, Veeshan. Classes unavailable: Druid, Enchanter*, Mage*, Monk*, Necro, Paladin, Ranger, SK.</P><P>Evil: Bertoxxulous, Cazic-Thule, Innoruuk, Rallos Zek. Classes unavailable: Druid, Paladin, Ranger.</P><P>At first impression, Good and Evil are roughly balanced. I think Evil got a better mix and secure home cities (only Neriak can possibly have even Neutral insurgents), but Good has more combinations and -- without knowing how skewed the population will be -- therefore greater numbers.</P><P>The Neutral faction is in big trouble. Unless Verant makes obvious balancing moves I expect nobody to play the Neutral team on purpose. Such moves might include moving Zek and/or Quellious and/or Prexus into Neutral or allowing Neutral to group with Good or Evil but not allowing Good and Evil to group with each other.</P><P>*I recall reading (but cannot find the quote) that there would be no agnostics allowed on the new PvP server. If agnostics are allowed and on the Neutral faction, then Neutral gets Enchanters, Mages, and Monks -- and becomes a tad more viable. Evil also loses its iron grip on Ogguk and Grobb, leaving Cabilis as the only secure home city.</P><P> </font></td>
